  m_SharedData: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 4c05b6e9c39e59b4c836029207039a98, type: 2}
  m_Metadata:
    m_Items: []
  m_TableData:
  - m_Id: 152900788979617792
    m_Localized: "OUR EQUIPMENT AT THE CORE OF \nDEFENSE ELECTRICAL ARCHITECTURES"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152908848712241152
    m_Localized: BACK
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031233101824
    m_Localized: BATTERY
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031258267648
    m_Localized: "<b>Scalability and Power</b>\nThe high-voltage battery system by
      Safran x Saft paves the way for a true revolution in onboard energy, thanks
      to packs connected in parallel reaching up to 800 VDC. These packs are configurable 
      to meet the power and energy requirements of the aircraft.\n\n<b>Modular Design</b>\nThe
      modules, adjustable in length to suit the requirements of each aircraft, are
      designed for seamless integration. Made from composite material with liquid
      cooling, they ensure advanced safety, adhering to the strict standards of the
      aerospace industry.\n\n<b>Innovative Cell Technology</b>\nThe LMFP-blend technology
      was selected as the first solution for its optimal balance between performance
      (280 Wh/kg, 2000 W/kg) and safety. Solid-state technology, targeting even higher
      performance levels (400 Wh/kg, 1600 W/kg) ) represents the next development
      stage. Pouch cell formats with opposing tabs are configurable from 15 Ah to
      55 Ah, allowing battery sizing adjustments by varying only the cell thickness.\n\n\u2022
      Unmatched Scalability and Power\n\n\u2022 Modular design\n\n\u2022 Innovative
      Electrochemistry, from LMFP-blend to Solid-State"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461952
    m_Localized: AC DISTRIBUTION
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461953
    m_Localized: "Electrical distribution is crucial for efficiently and safely powering
      all onboard systems. It provides power to standard equipment such as lighting
      and air conditioning, as well as critical systems like avionics and flight
      controls. \n\nThe system is designed with redundancies and backup solutions
      to ensure continuous availability, even during failures. Safety is enhanced
      by protections against overloads and short circuits, as well as real-time monitoring
      tools to identify and isolate faults. Thus, the electrical distribution ensures
      the efficiency, reliability, and safety of aviation operations.\n\n\u2022 Continuous
      power supply\n\n\u2022 Fault protection\n\n\u2022 System reliability"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461954
    m_Localized: DC DISTRIBUTION
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461955
    m_Localized: "Electrical distribution is crucial for efficiently and safely powering
      all onboard systems. It provides power to standard equipment such as lighting
      and air conditioning, as well as critical systems like avionics and flight
      controls. \n\nThe system is designed with redundancies and backup solutions
      to ensure continuous availability, even during failures. Safety is enhanced
      by protections against overloads and short circuits, as well as real-time monitoring
      tools to identify and isolate faults. Thus, the electrical distribution ensures
      the efficiency, reliability, and safety of aviation operations.\n\n\u2022 Continuous
      power supply\n\n\u2022 Fault protection\n\n\u2022 System reliability"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461956
    m_Localized: LHBCU
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461957
    m_Localized: "The Low High Bidirectional Charger Unit (LHBCU) is a high-performance
      bidirectional converter that interfaces an 800 VDC network with a 28 VDC network,
      delivering an exceptional efficiency of > 97%. \n\nThe available power can
      be adapted according to need by paralleling modules. It is capable of interfacing
      with various types of electrical networks, charging a battery, and incorporates
      reinforced isolation solutions in compliance with the most stringent safety
      requirements.\n\n\u2022 Bidirectionnal conversion\n\n\u2022 Exceptional efficiency\n\n\u2022
      Enhanced safety"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461958
    m_Localized: GENeUS 300
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461959
    m_Localized: "GENeUS 300 is the first product in the family of high-speed smart
      motors/generators. \n\nIt's a permanent magnet synchronous machine. Addressing
      high-power challenges, it enables the powering of an HVDC network for HV loads
      (landing gear, eTaxi, de-icing...) and/or for propulsion electric motors\u2014with
      the TGEN600 incorporating two GENeUS 300 units. Active current management is
      designed to meet the demanding requirements of electrical networks and ensure
      current stability in challenging environments. \n\nGENeUS 300 can be configured
      as two independent channels. GENeUS high-speed intelligent motor/generators
      are part of the ePower range, covering the entire electric propulsion chain
      and designed for hybrid and all-electric aircraft. It is also an ideal candidate
      for TurboFan hybridization for integration on the high-pressure shaft.\n\n\u2022
      High-speed dual channels\n\n\u2022 Stable current management\n\n\u2022 Suited
      for hybrid aircraft"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461960
    m_Localized: VFSG
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461962
    m_Localized: HVDC
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461963
    m_Localized: "Electrical distribution is crucial for efficiently and safely powering
      all onboard systems. It provides power to standard equipment such as lighting
      and air conditioning, as well as critical systems like avionics and flight
      controls. \n\nThe system is designed with redundancies and backup solutions
      to ensure continuous availability, even during failures. Safety is enhanced
      by protections against overloads and short circuits, as well as real-time monitoring
      tools to identify and isolate faults. Thus, the electrical distribution ensures
      the efficiency, reliability, and safety of aviation operations.\n\n\u2022 Continuous
      power supply\n\n\u2022 Fault protection\n\n\u2022 System reliability"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461964
    m_Localized: MCU
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461965
    m_Localized: "This reversible converter enables the control of electric motors
      (landing gear, eTaxi, compressor, de-icing) from an HVDC network. \n\nThe Motor
      Controller Units (MCU) are built around the best technologies available on
      the market, achieving power densities of around 10 kW/kg for harsh environments
      (non-pressurized engine zones).\n\n The MCUs cover a range from a few kW up
      to 250 kW with different cooling technologies (air or liquid).\n\n\u2022 Reversible
      converter\n\n\u2022 High power density\n\n\u2022 Adaptable cooling system"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031262461967
    m_Localized: "The Network Converter, is a converter that enables, for example,
      the interfacing of a propulsive HVDC network with another non-propulsive 115
      VAC or 230 VAC network, to fully leverage the potential of new hybrid technologies.
      \n\nThis converter incorporates a highly reliable reinforced galvanic isolation
      that ensures an exceptional level of safety. \n\nThe converter shares common
      building blocks with the MCUs and TRUs, drawing from Safran\u2019s expertise
      and experience.\n\n\u2022 Multi-network interfacing\n\n\u2022 Reinforced galvanic
      isolation\n\n\u2022 Enhanced safety"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152936031266656256
    m_Localized: "The Transformer Rectifier Unit (TRU) is designed to modify voltage
      levels. It can convert an input of 115V AC or 230V AC into an isolated 28V
      output with currents up to 400 ADC. TRUs are passive converters, meaning they
      operate purely autonomously, without complex components.\n\nThis characteristic,
      combined with Safran's expertise and experience, allows them to achieve exceptional
      reliability levels, with MTBF (Mean Time Between Failures) reaching several
      million flight hours. \n\nAdditionally, Safran has developed solutions for
      reducing acoustic noise and enhanced isolation solutions, enabling the TRU
      to be installed in the most demanding environments in terms of safety and comfort.\n\n\u2022
      Exceptional reliability\n\n\u2022 High current output\n\n\u2022 Low acoustic
      noise"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 152939225816354816
    m_Localized: "GENeUS VFSG represents a major breakthrough in variable frequency
      generator technology using synchronous machines with wound rotors.\n\nIt does
      not incorporate rare earth magnets in the main rotor. The generator supplies
      both 115V and 230V networks on the platform.\n\_\nIt enhances competitiveness
      in terms of weight and size, while increasing the energy efficiency of the
      machines.\n\n\_\u2022 Main rotor is magnet-free\n\n\_\u2022 Configurable in
      115V/230V modes\n\n\_\u2022 Outstanding power quality"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
